# ORIG TITLE    Top French lawyer found dead . 
# ORIG CONTENT  One of the most high-profile lawyers in France has been found dead on a beach in Brittany. Among his clients, 64-year-old Olivier Metzner defended the Societe Generale rogue trader Jerome Kerviel and Continental Airlines when it was accused of causing the Paris Concorde crash as well as former Panamanian dictator Manuel Noriega. A police source said a suicide note was found at Metzner’s house. A colleague, Antonin Levy, said Metzner’s death represented a huge loss to the French bar, calling him a “great lawyer and a fighter”. 
